docs.abstract: The opening of Amazon Go was alarming for many retailers, who saw a sudden willingness by Amazon to wield its power in new ways.
docs.snippet: The opening of Amazon Go was alarming for many retailers, who saw a sudden willingness by Amazon to wield its power in new ways.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — To see what it’s like inside stores where sensors and artificial intelligence have replaced cashiers, shoppers have to trek to Amazon Go, the internet retailer’s experimental convenience shop in downtown Seattle.

headline.main: Retailers Race Against Amazon to Automate Stores

byline.original: By Nick Wingfield, Paul Mozur and Michael Corkery

docs.abstract: The self-declared Grand Duchess Maria, a descendant of Russian royalty, took it upon herself to issue a bitter critique of the fictional Amazon series.
docs.snippet: The self-declared Grand Duchess Maria, a descendant of Russian royalty, took it upon herself to issue a bitter critique of the fictional Amazon series.
docs.lead_paragraph: “The Romanoffs,” Amazon’s new drama series in which characters are descendants of Russia’s royal family, has not received the best reviews.

headline.main: A Romanov Is Not Too Happy With ‘The Romanoffs’

docs.abstract: It was a technological wonder — until the retail landscape changed and new innovation, and greedy owners, arrived.
docs.snippet: It was a technological wonder — until the retail landscape changed and new innovation, and greedy owners, arrived.
docs.lead_paragraph: The orders poured in from everywhere — 105,000 a day at one point — so much so that the company became an economic force. It could make or break suppliers by promoting their products. It could dictate terms on manufacturing. Its headquarters city boomed as this tech-driven retailer built huge warehouses and factories and attracted other businesses and rivals. State and local governments complained that the company was harming small-town retailers.

headline.main: How Sears Was the Amazon of Its Day
headline.print_headline: How Sears Was the Amazon of Its Day

docs.abstract: The stock market continued to plunge Monday, as investors were unnerved by the unpredictable White House. Stocks are now down 4 percent this year.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Trump Bump is becoming the Trump Slump.

headline.print_headline: Stocks Sink As a Bump Gives Way To a Bear

docs.abstract: Here’s what the Amazon founder’s vast fortune tells us about the economic concentration of the tech industry — and how he might help unravel that for the world.
docs.snippet: Here’s what the Amazon founder’s vast fortune tells us about the economic concentration of the tech industry — and how he might help unravel that for the world.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jeff Bezos, the founder of Amazon and the world’s wealthiest man, has been publicly agonizing over a vexing problem: what to do with all his money.

headline.main: Why Jeff Bezos Should Push for Nobody to Get as Rich as Jeff Bezos
headline.print_headline: How Bezos Can Help Prevent the Next Bezos

docs.abstract: The European Union’s antitrust chief announced an inquiry into the e-commerce giant over its use of data collected about third-party merchants.
docs.snippet: The European Union’s antitrust chief announced an inquiry into the e-commerce giant over its use of data collected about third-party merchants.
docs.lead_paragraph: For many independent merchants who sell their goods on Amazon, there has long been deep concern that if the e-commerce giant saw a particular product selling well, the company would duplicate it, but at a lower price.

headline.main: Amazon Dominates as a Merchant and Platform. Europe Sees Reason to Worry.
headline.print_headline: Europe to Investigate Amazon’s Dual Role of Merchant and Platform

docs.abstract: Two days into a strike by antiquarian booksellers against the Amazon unit AbeBooks, the company capitulated.
docs.snippet: Two days into a strike by antiquarian booksellers against the Amazon unit AbeBooks, the company capitulated.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — A worldwide strike by antiquarian booksellers against an Amazon subsidiary proved successful after two days, with the retailer apologizing and saying it would cancel the actions that prompted the protest.

headline.main: After Protest, Booksellers Are Victorious Against Amazon Subsidiary
headline.print_headline: Antiquarian Booksellers Succeed in Strike Against Amazon Subsidiary

docs.abstract: Maya Rudolph and Fred Armisen play a couple stuck in a routine, in an Amazon series that is anything but that.
docs.snippet: Maya Rudolph and Fred Armisen play a couple stuck in a routine, in an Amazon series that is anything but that.
docs.lead_paragraph: One year, after 14 straight annual fishing trips, June (Maya Rudolph) and Oscar (Fred Armisen) decide to change up their routine and go skiing. Neither of them has ever skied before. They are middle-aged. It is perhaps too late for all this. They find themselves, freezing and unsteady, tottering on a bunny hill.

headline.main: Review: ‘Forever’ Is a Thrilling Story of Boring Love
headline.print_headline: Hey, You Two: Try Something New
